-as-per-vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235512\/master-bedroom-design-as-per-vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235512\/master-bedroom-design-as-per-vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235512\/master-bedroom-design-as-per-vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Design your master bedroom with soft colours and natural elements<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/colour-combination-for-bedroom-according-to-vastu\/\">Best Colour Combination For Bedroom According To Vastu<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Dimension as per Vastu<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Another crucial aspect is the master bedroom dimension. Ideally, the room should be square or rectangular. This shape facilitates an even distribution of energy. Avoid irregular shapes, as they can cause imbalance and stress.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235520\/master-bedroom-dimension-as-per-Vastu.jpg\" alt=\"Vastu-compliant master bedroom should have square or rectangular dimensions for even energy distribution and balance\" class=\"wp-image-58227\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235520\/master-bedroom-dimension-as-per-Vastu.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235520\/master-bedroom-dimension-as-per-Vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235520\/master-bedroom-dimension-as-per-Vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235520\/master-bedroom-dimension-as-per-Vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235520\/master-bedroom-dimension-as-per-Vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Use vastu principles to ensure balanced energy distribution<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Say goodbye to troubled sleep with our bedroom vastu tips\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/09110523\/say-goodbye-to-troubled-sleep-with-our-bedroom-vastu-tips.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Placement as per Vastu<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The master bedroom placement, as per Vastu, is typically recommended in the southwest corner of the house. This placement is believed to bring stability and strength to homeowners. Ideally, this is the direction in which, if the master bedroom is located, the homeowners will prosper. The servant room should never be in this direction.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235551\/master-bedroom-placement-as-per-vastu.jpg\" alt=\"Master bedroom placement as per Vastu: southwest corner for stability and strength, avoiding servant room in this direction\" class=\"wp-image-58230\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235551\/master-bedroom-placement-as-per-vastu.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235551\/master-bedroom-placement-as-per-vastu-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235551\/master-bedroom-placement-as-per-vastu-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235551\/master-bedroom-placement-as-per-vastu-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235551\/master-bedroom-placement-as-per-vastu-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A bedroom positioned according to Vastu<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Master Bedroom Layout as per Vastu\/Feng Shui\u00a0<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For east-facing homes, the master bedroom layout, as per Vastu east-facing house should still ideally be in the southwest corner. This ensures the room receives adequate sunlight and maintains balance within the home. The layout involves several key elements, including the placement of the bed, furniture, and other essentials to ensure a free flow of energy, promoting peace and good vibes.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some handy tips to get the layout right:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Bed Placement<\/strong>: Place the bed away from the door, but ensure it is easily visible from the entrance. This position promotes a sense of security and control.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Mirrors<\/strong>: Avoid placing mirrors opposite the bed as they can cause disturbances in sleep.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Electronic Devices<\/strong>: Minimize the presence of electronic devices in the bedroom to reduce electromagnetic interference.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Lighting<\/strong>: Use soft and dim lighting to create a relaxing atmosphere. Natural light is also beneficial, so ensure the room has adequate windows.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Interiors<\/strong>: Include elements that resonate with personal happiness and peace, such as family photos, positive artwork, and calming plants.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235542\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-feng-shui.jpg\" alt=\"Master bedroom layout per Vastu: Place bed away from the door, avoid mirrors opposite, use soft lighting, and add calming decor\" class=\"wp-image-58229\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235542\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-feng-shui.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235542\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-feng-shui-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235542\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-feng-shui-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235542\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-feng-shui-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/11235542\/master-bedroom-layout-as-per-vastu-feng-shui-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Getting the layout right can result in a harmonious home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a balanced living space is essential for overall well-being. Vastu Shastra, an ancient Indian architectural science, offers guidelines to enhance the positive energy in your home. The master bedroom, being a sanctuary for rest and rejuvenation, should be designed meticulously. By following these guidelines for the master bedroom layout, as per Vastu, you can create a space that promotes restful sleep and enhances overall well-being. For more tips and information on how to place your master bedroom right, reach out to our experts here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">Contact Us | Home Interior Design | DesignCafe<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs on Master Bedroom Layout as Per Vastu<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. How should the shape and size of the master bedroom be designed according to Vastu principles?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Vastu, the master bedroom should ideally be square or rectangular to ensure balanced energy flow. Avoid irregular shapes, as they can create imbalance and stress. The room size should be proportionate to the overall house, ideally larger than other bedrooms, symbolizing stability and strength.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. What are the Vastu recommendations for colours and materials used in the master bedroom?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Vastu recommends using soft, soothing colours like shades of blue, green, or earthy tones in the master bedroom. These colours promote joy and relaxation. Natural materials like wood and cotton are preferred. Avoid using synthetic materials and dark colours, which can disrupt the peaceful vibe.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. Are there specific directions that are considered auspicious for placing the master bedroom?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, the southwest corner of the house is considered the most auspicious placement for the master bedroom. This direction is believed to bring the homeowners stability, strength, and good health. Sleeping with the head towards the south or west is also recommended to align with the earth&#8217;s magnetic field.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. What are the ideal placements for the bed, doors, and windows in a Vastu-compliant master bedroom?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In a Vastu-compliant master bedroom, the bed should be placed with the head towards the south or west. Doors should be positioned to avoid direct alignment with the bed, promoting privacy and security. Windows are best placed on the north or east walls to ensure proper ventilation and natural light.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. Can Vastu principles be adapted to accommodate modern amenities and design preferences in the master bedroom?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, Vastu principles can be adapted to modern designs. Integrate modern amenities while maintaining key Vastu guidelines such as bed placement, room shape, and colour schemes. The goal is to balance functionality with harmony, ensuring the room remains a peaceful and energy-efficient sanctuary.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t